data.name: EllipticalArc
desc: This structure specifies an arbitrary elliptical arc.
This structure contains all parameters necessary to specify arbitrary elliptical arcs. The parameters are modeled closely after the SVG specification.

As with the parameters below, there are mostly four different ellipses arcs (two different ellipses, on which four different arcs connect start and end point) which satisfy the given set of constrains. Thus, there are two flags indicating which one of those ellipses should be taken.

items.name: IsClockwiseSweep
lines: If TRUE, and there's a choice, take the arc that goes clock-wise from start to end point.

items.name: IsLargeArc
lines: If TRUE, and there's a choice, take the longer one of two arcs connecting start and end point.

items.name: RadiusX
lines: Main radius in x direction of the ellipse this arc is part of.

items.name: RadiusY
lines: Main radius in y direction of the ellipse this arc is part of.

items.name: XAxisRotation
lines: Rotation angle of the x axis of the ellipse relative to the x axis of the reference coordinate system.
